Package psi.exception

Contains the exceptions thrown by the SDK.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CustomRuntimeException
    A generic unchecked exception that is thrown whenever an unexpected and or/not compliant condition occurs.
    InvalidPsiClientKeyDescriptionException
    This exception is thrown whenever the user is trying to generate a generic PsiClientKeyDescription, but the input parameters are not compliant with any of the available algorithms.
    KeyGenerationException
    This exception is thrown whenever an external key is not provided by the user and the sdk is not able to generate by itself a new one.
    PsiClientException
    This exception is thrown whenever an unexpected and not compliant condition occurs when creating the client objects or performing client operations, e.g., missing or incompatible keys.
    PsiServerException
    This exception is thrown whenever an unexpected and not compliant condition occurs when loading the server objects or performing server operations, e.g., missing psiCacheProvider implementation while it is enabled.
    PsiServerInitException
    This exception is thrown whenever some data required to initialize a server session is missing or not compliant with respect to the sdk logic, e.g., missing keys.
    UnsupportedKeySizeException
    This exception is thrown whenever the server attempts to initialize a session with an unsupported key size, or when a client attempts to load a session associated to an unsupported key size.
    UnsupportedKeySizeRuntimeException
    This exception is thrown whenever the UnsupportedKeySize exception is not generated by an external input (e.g, sent by the client) but due to internal errors.

Package psi.exception Description

Contains the exceptions thrown by the SDK.
